The paper addresses the problem of robotic grasping and manipulation, which is a core topic in robotics. The focus is on dealing with uncertainty due to noisy sensing, inaccurate models, and hard-to-predict environment dynamics, which are common challenges in robotics. The paper also emphasizes the importance of real-time perception and its integration with reactive motion generation methods, which are key topics in the field of robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) techniques, which are relevant to the problem of perception and motion planning. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed methods on a real robotic platform, which involves control and system engineering (cs.SY).
